#   DIFF-008: tree-diff silently truncates later files тАФ per-file BASS scratch is never rewound in `graf_diff_tree_refs_inner`

The per-file loops in `graf_diff_tree_refs_inner` call `GRAFDiff2Layer` with NO
`call()`/`try()` frame: the `ok64` return is IGNORED, and `GRAFDiff2Layer`'s internal
BASS scratch is not rewound between files. So scratch accumulates across the file
list until `a_carve` returns NOROOM тАФ and from then on every remaining file's diff
SILENTLY FAILS and is dropped from the output. A big-blob file (or just enough
files) thus truncates the tail of a `be diff:`/`commit:` tree diff with no error.
Surfaced by [BLAME-006b] (a 9.5 MB binary starved the last file); its binary-skip
MASKED the trigger but did not fix the root. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  `graf/DIFFREF.c::graf_diff_tree_refs_inner` (`:513`) тАФ the added/changed-file loop
    (`:555-589`) and the deletion loop (`:592-612`) each end in a BARE
    `GRAFDiff2Layer(path, ext, old_data, new_data, NO, navver);` (`:588`, `:611`) тАФ
    the return is discarded, so a per-file NOROOM/failure is swallowed, not propagated.
 -  `GRAFDiff2Layer` (`:155`) does `GRAFArenaInit` + the weave carves (e.g. the wt-base
    wrapper `a_carve(u8, base_buf, 16<<20)` `:217`; `WEAVEEmitFull` carves the 65536
    `outtoks` etc.). None of that is released between loop iterations тАФ there is no
    per-file `try()` rewind or `Bu8mark`/rewind. The code comment at `:370-372`
    documents the failure mode: "carves 16 MB per file тАФ until `a_carve` returns NOROOM
    and the outer call frame unwinds."
 -  Symptom (from [BLAME-006b]): on the root-tree diff, the LAST file
    (`beagle/test/be-unknown-command.sh`) was silently truncated because the 9.5 MB
    `dog/dogs.png` weave had exhausted the BASS. BLAME-006b's binary-skip removed THAT
    trigger but a large-enough text set (or many files) still truncates the tail.

### Goals
 -  Each per-file diff runs inside its OWN BASS frame so its scratch is released before
    the next file тАФ scratch is bounded to one file's worth, not the cumulative tree.
 -  A per-file `GRAFDiff2Layer` failure is propagated/surfaced (or at minimum logged),
    NEVER silently swallowed into a truncated-but-exit-0 diff.

### Constraints
 -  Output byte-identical on inputs that fit today; the fix only removes the
    accumulation. graf change gates for review. Keep the [BLAME-006b] binary-skip +
    one-sided short-circuit intact.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  (open) Wrap each per-file `GRAFDiff2Layer` in a `try()`/`then` frame (rewinds BASS to
    the pre-call mark after each file) тАФ the canonical PRO.h pattern тАФ or take an explicit
    `Bu8mark` before the call and rewind after. Stop ignoring the return: `call()`/`try()`
    it so NOROOM/failure propagates instead of truncating.

