##  Outcome
 -  *LANDED `b9ef44b2`* (FF child of `d6f35358`; 306/306): each per-file
    `GRAFDiff2Layer` at `graf/DIFFREF.c:588/611` is now `call()`-wrapped (rewinds
    ABC_BASS per file + propagates a per-file NOROOM); `test/diff/17-tree-no-truncate`.
    (First cut used `try(тАж); nedo done;` тАФ identical to `call()` per `abc/PRO.h:77/97`;
    tightened to plain `call()`.) Root cause confirmed тАФ
    `GRAFDiff2Layer`'s weave carves a FIXED ~17 MB BASS block per file; with no
    surrounding frame, scratch accumulated until `a_carve` NOROOM at ~58 files, after
    which every remaining file's diff silently failed (return ignored) and was dropped
    (exit 0). Fix (`graf/DIFFREF.c:588` + `:611`): `try(GRAFDiff2Layer,тАж); nedo done;` тАФ
    `try()` rewinds ABC_BASS per file (bounds scratch to one file), `nedo done`
    propagates a genuine NOROOM instead of truncating. REDтЖТGREEN `test/diff/17-tree-no-truncate`
    (80 tiny files: unfixed truncates at `f056`/drops `f079`; fixed renders all 80).
    Small-set output byte-identical, perf unchanged, BLAME-006b/DIFF-001/002 intact.
    *306/306*. Awaiting gate. Msg: `DIFF-008: per-file try() frame in tree-diff; no truncation`.

